0.title: Focus on Selling Online
0.content: ShipBlu Docs offers a developer API for ShipBlu last-mile delivery service. It is intended to be used by Merchants who have an account on ShipBlu, and would like to integrate their online e-commerce store to our delivery service. Get started now . ShipBlu makes last-mile delivery predictable by using advanced combinatorial optimization methods to get packages to customers in time. Our services are exposed in APIs that you can directly use from your e-commerce website. If you need help streamlining your online sales process, this is the right place. Don’t have in-house developers? We can always help. Get in touch at tech@shipblu.com .

2.content: IN this part you will know only two things to deal with ShipBlu API’s . | Getting Your API Key | Test Your Setup | . Don’t waste a lot of time and let’s go.

6.title: ShipBlu API Tutorial
6.content: In this tutorial we will tell a story of a merchant who wants to integrate their online e-commerce store to our delivery service. Before start we need to introduce only two major concept: . | Customer Agent (CA): Is a person that deliver shipment to customer. | Merchant Agent (MA): Is a person that deal with merchant. | . After we introduce above two concepts let’s don’t waste a lot of time and let’s start. We will start tutorial by passing on following points: . geo availability, to service availability to placing an orders and viewing orders.

7.title: Geo Availability
7.content: ShipBlu offers four major concepts that illustrate geo availability that introduce it. | Governorates . ShipBlu introduce his service in all egypt governorates from Alexandria to Aswan. You can deliver your shipment to any place in egypt without any headache about how deliver it. | Cities & Zones . AS we know each governorate has many cities, and each city consist of some zones. For good ShipBlu can deliver your shipment to any place within city. | PUDOs . We can define PUDOs as drop off points that CA can drop shipments on it and the Customer receive it from this PUDO. ShipBlu provide this service to save merchant and customer order shipment cost. | . You can discover geo availability ShipBlu APIs from here. Now after we talked about geo availability and how ShipBlu categories it and deal with it. let’s talk about other concept called service availability.

8.title: Service Availability
8.content: Service availability is the services that ShipBlu can introduce it to merchants. This services is represented in the following points: . | Service Level . ShipBlu introduce service level concept that determine periods that shipment delivered to customer within. Service level determined by merchant based on his governorate and subscription, it consist of four categories. Availabel service level: . | overnight | 2 days | 3 to 5 days | 5 to 7 days | . | Package Size . ShipBlu introduce two package size option: . | Small Flyer (25x35cm) | Large Flyer (50x45cm) | . | Handshake Type . ShipBlu introduce handshake type concept that determine how CA will deliver shipment to customer. it consist of two categories: . | D2D (Door To Door) . From its name, CA will deliver shipment to customer door. | PUDO . As we mention PUDO is drop off points that CA can drop shipments on it and the Customer receive it from this point. | . | . You can discover service availability ShipBlu APIs from here. Now after we talked about geo availability and service availability. let’s talk about how placing an orders and viewing it.

9.title: Orders
9.content: ShipBlu introduce awesome features to merchant to control his orders. Before discover these features let’s talk shortly and quickly about orders types. Orders are divided into three categoricals: . | Delivery . Delivery order: is order that merchant want to deliver it to customer. | Return . Return order: is order that merchant want to get it from customer. | Exchanges . exchange order: is order to deliver shipment to customer and get another shipment from him. | . Now after we talked about orders types, Let’s discover these features together: . | List all orders . Merchant can show all (delivery, return, and exchange) orders info that he has created its. | Create new one . Merchant can create new (delivery, return, and exchange) orders. | Retrieve specific one . Merchant can show specific (delivery, return, and exchange) order info. | Update specific one . Merchant can update all info of specific (delivery, return, and exchange) order. | Partial update specific one . Merchant can update some info of specific (delivery, return, and exchange) order. | Delete update specific one . Merchant can delete specific (delivery, return, and exchange) order. | . You can discover ShipBlu APIs of all above features from following links: . | Delivery | Return | Exchanges | . There is other feature ShipBlu introduce it to merchant to save his time to create multiple delivery order. | Create multiple delivery orders . This feature divides into two steps: . | Download template file . In this step you can download delivery order template file to add multiple delivery orders. | Upload template file . In this step you can create your multiple delivery orders by upload this file. | . | . You can discover this feature from here . And you can discover more full features that ShipBlu introduce it to merchant from API Reference page.
